This paper discusses network coding-based link failure recovery techniques, which are primarily related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The paper also discusses coding techniques and design algorithms, which are related to distributed computing (DC) and signal processing (SI). Finally, the paper discusses capacity efficiency, which is related to computer communication (CC). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NI and cs.IT, followed by cs.DC, cs.SI, and cs.CC.
